name: Still Life 4.0
description:
Fizz Pop (b.1974)  
2009  
12000 x 9600 pixels  
Source: Hans Bollongier, Still Life with Flowers, 1639, oil on panel, 68cm x 54.5 cm  

  The Golden Age of painting documents the first speculative bubble, a historic period with significant parallels to the current crypto movement.  The tulips in Still Life 4.0 are digital interpretations of the Semper Augustus tulip, the most valuable tulip during Tulip Mania; it’s stunning red & white petals are the result of a tulip mosaic virus.
  In 2009 this piece was offered as a limited edition of 7 cibachrome prints.  Before the cibachrome print was discontinued only one from the edition was produced & sold.
